    <h2>Context & Collaboration</h2>
    <div class="grid bg-fill">
      <div>
        <h3>Overview</h3>
        <p><strong>IQ Marketer</strong> is designed to streamline workflows for marketers who currently rely on multiple tools and manual processes for their daily tasks. Our goal is to create a seamless, integrated experience that enhances efficiency and collaboration between marketing and sales teams.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>TEAMS</h3>
        <div>
          <div><strong>Product, UX, Visual Design</strong> Yenny Y & Zitian Zhou</div>
          <div><strong>Content Designer</strong> Jessica Gonsiewski</div>
          <div><strong>Product owner</strong> Hannah Cox & Ana Rachel Garcia </div>
          <div><strong>Project length</strong> Three months</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid bg-fill">
      <div>
        <h3>PRIMARY OBJECTIVE</h3>
        <p><strong>Deliver integrated sales, marketing and execution capabilities that drive front office efficiencies and increase time focused on clients</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>DIGITAL MARKETING OBJECTIVE</h3>
        <p>Digital Marketing and Client Engagement Leveraging Digital Marketing capabilities to <strong>support world class client engagement and acquisition</strong>—increasing marketing's influence on new pipeline and deepening within existing relationships</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <hr>
  <section>
    <div class="details">
      <div>
        <h3>PROBLEM</h3>
        <p>Marketers needs to <strong>navigate multiple fragmented tools and inefficient processes to manage their daily tasks.</strong> With Salesforce being phased out the following year, integrating campaign creation into IQ Marketer is essential to streamline workflows and support teams like Marketing Delivery or marketing automation specialists.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>CHALLENGE</h3>
        <p><strong>Merging three CRMs—Salesforce, Dash Nominator, and GEM—into IQ for Marketing delivery team and integrating Stova for event campaigns or event planner personas.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>HOW MIGHT WE</h3>
        <p><strong></strong>How might we</strong> integrate fragmented tools like Dash Nominator, Salesforce, Gem, and Stova into a single IQ platform to streamline marketers’ daily tasks efficiently?</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>SOLUTION</h3>
        <p>Our primary goal is to develop campaign creation capabilities within IQ Marketer to replace Salesforce’s functionalities and better support the sales and banker teams. To ensure our design meets business needs, we collaborate closely with product marketing to define workflows, pain points, and requirements while considering scalability. </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
